                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>6</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13550619" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2013 00:41:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We rely on that to reassign regions where they were when HBase restarts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13550651" author="sershe" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2013 01:04:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can we do it during normal operation close, e.g. when master tells server to close the region?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13550847" author="stack" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2013 05:40:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sershe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sershe&quot;&gt;Sergey Shelukhin&lt;/a&gt; Yes, if you can distingush cluster shutdown from master explicit close.  What does client do if no address for a region?  Give up or retry?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13551331" author="sershe" created="Fri, 11 Jan 2013 18:08:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt; it retries with wait, which is probably the desired behavior if region is being opened somewhere&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13650360" author="sershe" created="Tue, 7 May 2013 01:51:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With RegionMovedException and RegionOpeningException, for normal case this is probably not relevant&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13650534" author="stack" created="Tue, 7 May 2013 05:45:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sershe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sershe&quot;&gt;Sergey Shelukhin&lt;/a&gt;, so you have been running your cluster for six months and you have to shut it down.  On restart, you want to regions assigned to the servers they had been running on the last 6 months because their data will be at these nodes.  The stochastic load balancer looks at what is in hdfs and tries to put regions where they have high locality but it will probably rarely do as well as current mechanism which has us try to put a region back at its old location (and we know the old location because we left it as the server on cluster shutdown up in meta table).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
